records.addlTxt: All other previously ordered terms and conditions of bail to continue.

Defendant Ryan BS Tate Jr. appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney John M Binder in court for Ryan BS Tate Jr.  Attorney Catelin Autumn Ringersma for John J Rejowski appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for bail/bond hearing. State has complied with victim notification; victim appeared by zoom. Court hears arguments as to bail. For reasons as set forth on the record, Court modifies bail to $20,000.00 cash; all other previously ordered terms and conditions of bail to continue. Court ordered case adjourned for one last status conference in Branch 04; VIA ZOOM. Status conference scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Ryan BS Tate Jr. not in court, in custody.  Attorney John M Binder appeared by video for Ryan BS Tate Jr.  Attorney John J Rejowski in court for State of Wisconsin. State advises does not have victim notification for defense's bail hearing. Case adjourned in Branch 4.

Defense advises withdraw of all motions and provided offer from the state. Defense requesting additional time for review of offer and request status date. Court grants. Case adjourned in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for September 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
